  <span id="freeText9347162692924438099" style="display:none">Alternate cover edition of ISBN <a href="https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/58144560-stones-from-the-river" rel="nofollow noopener">9780684844770</a><br /><br />From the highly acclaimed, award-winning author of <i>Floating in My Mother's Palm</i> comes a stunning novel about ordinary people living in extraordinary times.<br /><br />Trudi Montag is a <i>Zwerg</i>—a dwarf—short, undesirable, different, the voice of anyone who has ever tried to fit in. Eventually she learns that being different is a secret that all humans share—from her mother who flees into madness, to her friend Georg whose parents pretend he's a girl, to the Jews Trudy harbors in her cellar.<br /><br />Ursula Hegi brings us a timeless and unforgettable story in Trudi and a small town, weaving together a profound tapestry of emotional power, humanity, and truth.</span>
